# DriftWatch — root .dockerignore
# All four service Dockerfiles use `context: .` (repo root) in docker-compose.yml,
# so this file controls what every image build sees. Keeps builds fast and
# prevents secrets / local state from ever landing in an image layer.

# --- Git ---
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# --- Secrets & local env ---
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# --- Python virtualenvs (large; never want in images) ---
.venv
**/.venv
env/
venv/
ENV/

# --- Python build / cache artifacts ---
**/__pycache__
**/*.py[cod]
**/*.egg-info
**/.pytest_cache
**/.ruff_cache
**/.mypy_cache
**/.coverage
**/htmlcov
build/
dist/

# --- Editor / OS junk ---
.idea
.vscode
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# --- Local-only docs (planning, brief, instructor examples) ---
docs - DO NOT COMMIT

# --- Local data / runtime state (compose volumes + MLflow local files) ---
postgres_data
redis_data
mlruns
mlartifacts
**/mlflow.db
*.rdb
*.aof

# --- Notebooks ---
**/.ipynb_checkpoints

# --- Markdown (keep README so images can reference it if needed) ---
*.md
!README.md